verses.text_plain: And the whole earth was of one language, and of one speech.
verses.verse_html:
1And the whole earth was of one language, and of one speech. ▼
▼ language: Heb. lip.
 , ▼
▼ speech: Heb. words

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, as they journeyed from the east, that they found a plain in the land of Shinar; and they dwelt there.
verses.verse_html:
2And it came to pass, as they journeyed from the east, that they found a plain in the land of Shinar; and they dwelt there. ▼
▼ from…: or, eastward

tokens.text: And it came to pass, as they journeyed

verses.text_plain: And they said one to another, Go to, let us make brick, and burn them throughly. And they had brick for stone, and slime had they for morter.
verses.verse_html:
3And they said one to another, Go to, let us make brick, and burn them throughly. And they had brick for stone, and slime had they for morter. ▼
▼ they said…: Heb. a man said to his neighbour
 , ▼
▼ burn…: Heb. burn them to a burning

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they said…: Heb. a man said to his neighbour
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they said…: Heb. a man said to his neighbour

footnotes.body_text: ▼ burn…: Heb. burn them to a burning
footnotes.body_html: ▼ burn…: Heb. burn them to a burning

verses.text_plain: And they said, Go to, let us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven; and let us make us a name, lest we be scattered abroad upon the face of the whole earth.
verses.verse_html: 4And they said, Go to, let us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven; and let us make us a name, lest we be scattered abroad upon the face of the whole earth.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of men builded.
verses.verse_html: 5And the Lord came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of men builded.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said, Behold, the people is one, and they have all one language; and this they begin to do: and now nothing will be restrained from them, which they have imagined to do.
verses.verse_html: 6And the Lord said, Behold, the people is one, and they have all one language; and this they begin to do: and now nothing will be restrained from them, which they have imagined to do.

tokens.text: from them, which they have imagined

verses.text_plain: Go to, let us go down, and there confound their language, that they may not understand one another’s speech.
verses.verse_html: 7Go to, let us go down, and there confound their language, that they may not understand one another’s speech.

verses.text_plain: So the Lord scattered them abroad from thence upon the face of all the earth: and they left off to build the city.
verses.verse_html: 8So the Lord scattered them abroad from thence upon the face of all the earth: and they left off to build the city.

verses.text_plain: Therefore is the name of it called Babel; because the Lord did there confound the language of all the earth: and from thence did the Lord scatter them abroad upon the face of all the earth.
verses.verse_html:
9Therefore is the name of it called Babel; because the Lord did there confound the language of all the earth: and from thence did the Lord scatter them abroad upon the face of all the earth. ▼
▼ Babel: that is, Confusion

tokens.text: Therefore is the name of it

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Babel: that is, Confusion

verses.text_plain: These are the generations of Shem: Shem was an hundred years old, and begat Arphaxad two years after the flood:
verses.verse_html: 10These are the generations of Shem: Shem was an hundred years old, and begat Arphaxad two years after the flood:

verses.text_plain: And Shem lived after he begat Arphaxad five hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 11And Shem lived after he begat Arphaxad five hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Arphaxad lived five and thirty years, and begat Salah:
verses.verse_html: 12And Arphaxad lived five and thirty years, and begat Salah:

verses.text_plain: And Arphaxad lived after he begat Salah four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 13And Arphaxad lived after he begat Salah four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Salah lived thirty years, and begat Eber:
verses.verse_html: 14And Salah lived thirty years, and begat Eber:

verses.text_plain: And Salah lived after he begat Eber four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 15And Salah lived after he begat Eber four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Eber lived four and thirty years, and begat Peleg:
verses.verse_html:
16And Eber lived four and thirty years, and begat Peleg: ▼
▼ Peleg: Gr. Phalec

verses.text_plain: And Eber lived after he begat Peleg four hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 17And Eber lived after he begat Peleg four hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Peleg lived thirty years, and begat Reu:
verses.verse_html: 18And Peleg lived thirty years, and begat Reu:

verses.text_plain: And Peleg lived after he begat Reu two hundred and nine years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 19And Peleg lived after he begat Reu two hundred and nine years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Reu lived two and thirty years, and begat Serug:
verses.verse_html:
20And Reu lived two and thirty years, and begat Serug: ▼
▼ Serug: Gr. Saruch

verses.text_plain: And Reu lived after he begat Serug two hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 21And Reu lived after he begat Serug two hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Serug lived thirty years, and begat Nahor:
verses.verse_html: 22And Serug lived thirty years, and begat Nahor:

verses.text_plain: And Serug lived after he begat Nahor two hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 23And Serug lived after he begat Nahor two hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Nahor lived nine and twenty years, and begat Terah:
verses.verse_html:
24And Nahor lived nine and twenty years, and begat Terah: ▼
▼ Terah: Gr. Thara

verses.text_plain: And Nahor lived after he begat Terah an hundred and nineteen years, and begat sons and daughters.
verses.verse_html: 25And Nahor lived after he begat Terah an hundred and nineteen years, and begat sons and daughters.

verses.text_plain: And Terah lived seventy years, and begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran.
verses.verse_html: 26And Terah lived seventy years, and begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran.

verses.text_plain: Now these are the generations of Terah: Terah begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran; and Haran begat Lot.
verses.verse_html: 27Now these are the generations of Terah: Terah begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran; and Haran begat Lot.

verses.text_plain: And Haran died before his father Terah in the land of his nativity, in Ur of the Chaldees.
verses.verse_html: 28And Haran died before his father Terah in the land of his nativity, in Ur of the Chaldees.

verses.text_plain: And Abram and Nahor took them wives: the name of Abram’s wife was Sarai; and the name of Nahor’s wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milcah, and the father of Iscah.
verses.verse_html: 29And Abram and Nahor took them wives: the name of Abram’s wife was Sarai; and the name of Nahor’s wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milcah, and the father of Iscah.

verses.text_plain: But Sarai was barren; she had no child.
verses.verse_html: 30But Sarai was barren; she had no child.

verses.text_plain: And Terah took Abram his son, and Lot the son of Haran his son’s son, and Sarai his daughter in law, his son Abram’s wife; and they went forth with them from Ur of the Chaldees, to go into the land of Canaan; and they came unto Haran, and dwelt there.
verses.verse_html: 31And Terah took Abram his son, and Lot the son of Haran his son’s son, and Sarai his daughter in law, his son Abram’s wife; and they went forth with them from Ur of the Chaldees, to go into the land of Canaan; and they came unto Haran, and dwelt there.

verses.text_plain: And the days of Terah were two hundred and five years: and Terah died in Haran.
verses.verse_html: 32And the days of Terah were two hundred and five years: and Terah died in Haran.
